HEADWORD: Anagrammatize
<hw>An`a*gram"ma*tize</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'anagrammati`zein</grk> cf. F. <ets>anagrammatiser</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To transpose, as the letters of a word, so as to form an
anagram.</def> <rj><au>Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

